Platforms

     * [https://github.com/cocaine]Cocaine - A cloud platform enabling you
       to build your own PaaS clouds.
     * [http://deis.io/]Deis - Open source application platform for public
       and private clouds.
     * [http://fabric8.io/]Fabric8 - Open source microservices platform
       based on Docker, Kubernetes and Jenkins. Makes it easy to create,
       edit, deploy and manage microservices and go faster.
     * [https://hook.io/]Hook.io - Open source provider of microservice
       and webhook hosting.
     * [https://www.lightbend.com/]Lightbend c - Platform for building
       scalable reactive systems on the JVM.
     * [https://github.com/mantl/mantl]Mantl - Platform for rapidly
       deploying globally distributed services.
     * [https://netflix.github.io/]Netflix OSS - Netflix open source
       software ecosystem.
     * [http://openwhisk.org/]OpenWhisk - Serverless, open source cloud
       platform that executes functions in response to events at any
       scale.
     * [https://stups.io/]STUPS - A set of tools and components by Zalando
       to provide a convenient and audit-compliant PaaS for multiple
       autonomous teams on top of AWS.
     * [http://vamp.io/]VAMP c - Build, deploy and manage microservices
       with power and ease.

Frameworks / Runtimes

     * [http://akka.io/]Akka - Toolkit and runtime for building highly
       concurrent, distributed, and resilient message-driven applications
       on the JVM.
     * [http://baratine.io/]Baratine - Platform for building a network of
       loosely-coupled POJO microservices.
     * [https://github.com/erlang/otp]Erlang/OTP - Programming language
       used to build massively scalable soft real-time systems with
       requirements on high availability.
     * [http://twitter.github.io/finagle]Finagle - Extensible RPC system
       for the JVM, used to construct high-concurrency servers.
     * [https://github.com/GPars/GPars]GPars - Concurrency and parallelism
       framework for the JVM.
     * [https://github.com/bitfinexcom/grenache]Grenache - A Bittorent-DHT
       based microservices framework supporting REQ/REP and PUB/SUB
       patterns over multiple transports.
     * [https://zeroc.com/]Ice - Comprehensive RPC framework with support
       for C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, Python, and more.
     * [https://github.com/lagom/lagom]Lagom - Reactive microservices for
       the JVM.
     * [https://github.com/networknt/light-java]Light Java - A fast,
       lightweight and more productive microservices framework.
     * [https://github.com/aol/micro-server]Microserver - Java 8 native,
       zero configuration, standards based, battle hardened library to run
       Java REST microservices.
     * [https://github.com/orbit/orbit]Orbit - Modern framework for JVM
       languages that makes it easier to build and maintain distributed
       and scalable online services.
     * [https://github.com/puniverse/quasar]Quasar - Fibers, channels and
       actors for the JVM.
     * [https://github.com/scalecube/scalecube]ScaleCube - Toolkit for
       building reactive microservices for the JVM: low-latency,
       high-throughput, scalable and resilient.
     * [http://vertx.io/]Vert.X - Toolkit for building reactive
       applications on the JVM.
     * [https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-microservices-toolbox]Vert.X
       Toolbox - A set of Vert.x components to build reactive microservice
       applications.
     * [https://github.com/facebook/wangle]Wangle - A framework providing
       a set of common client/server abstractions for building services in
       a consistent, modular, and composable way.
     * [http://wildfly-swarm.io/]WildFly Swarm - Microservices starting
       with just enough Java EE runtime, based on
       [https://projects.eclipse.org/proposals/eclipse-microprofile]Eclips
       e MicroProfile.

Service Toolkits

Polyglot

     * [https://github.com/apex/apex]Apex - Tool for deploying and
       managing AWS Lambda functions. With shims for languages not yet
       supported by Lambda, you can use Golang out of the box.
     * [http://coap.technology/impls.html]CoAP - Constrained application
       protocol implementations.
     * [http://www.grpc.io/]GRPC - A high performance, open source,
       general RPC framework that puts mobile and HTTP/2 first. Libraries
       in C, C++, Java, Go, Node.js, Python, Ruby, Objective-C, PHP and
       C#.
     * [http://github.com/hprose]Hprose - A very newbility RPC Library,
       support 25+ languages now.

C

     * [https://kore.io/]Kore - Easy to use web application framework for
       writing scalable web APIs in C.
     * [https://github.com/wolkykim/libasyncd/]Libasyncd - Embeddable
       event-based asynchronous HTTP server library for C.
     * [http://libslack.org/]Libslack - Provides a generic agent oriented
       programming model, run time selection of locking strategies,
       functions that make writing daemons trivial and simplify the
       implementation of network servers and clients, &c.
     * [http://lwan.ws/]Lwan - High-performance and scalable web server.
     * [https://github.com/davidmoreno/onion]Onion - C library to create
       simple HTTP servers and web applications.
     * [https://github.com/Adaptv/ribs2]RIBS2 - Library which allows
       building high-performance internet serving systems.

C++

     * [https://github.com/sgieseking/anyrpc]AnyRPC - Provides a common
       system to work with a number of different remote procedure call
       standards, including: JSON-RPC, XML-RPC, MessagePack-RPC.
     * [https://capnproto.org/cxxrpc.html]Cap'n Proto RPC - The Cap'n
       Proto C++ RPC implementation.
     * [http://cppmicroservices.org/]C++ Micro Services - An OSGi-like C++
       dynamic module system and service registry.
     * [https://github.com/endurox-dev/endurox/]Enduro/X - XATMI based
       service framework for GNU/Linux.
     * [https://github.com/splunk/pion]Pion - C++ framework for building
       lightweight HTTP interfaces.
     * [https://github.com/oktal/pistache]Pistache - A high-performance
       REST toolkit written in C++.
     * [http://pocoproject.org/]Poco - C++ class libraries for building
       network-based applications and servers.
     * [https://github.com/Corvusoft/restbed]Restbed - Brings asynchronous
       RESTful functionality to C++11 applications.
     * [https://github.com/datasift/served]Served - C++ library for
       building high-performance RESTful web servers.
     * [https://github.com/stefanocasazza/ULib]ULib - Highly optimized
       class framework for writing C++ applications.

CSharp

     * [http://getakka.net/]Akka.NET - Toolkit and runtime for building
       highly concurrent, distributed, and fault tolerant event-driven
       applications on .NET & Mono.
     * [http://nancyfx.org/]Nancy - Lightweight web framework.

D

     * [http://vibed.org/]Vibe.d - Asynchronous I/O that doesn't get in
       your way, written in D.

Erlang VM

Elixir

     * [http://www.phoenixframework.org/]Phoenix - Framework for building
       HTML5 apps, API backends and distributed systems.
     * [https://github.com/elixir-lang/plug]Plug - A specification and
       conveniences for composable modules between web applications.

Erlang

     * [https://github.com/ninenines/cowboy]Cowboy - Small, fast, modular
       HTTP server written in Erlang.
     * [https://github.com/mochi/mochiweb]Mochiweb - Erlang library for
       building lightweight HTTP servers.

Go

     * [https://echo.labstack.com/]Echo - Fast and unfancy HTTP server
       framework for Go. Up to 10x faster than the rest.
     * [https://github.com/nytimes/gizmo]Gizmo - Microservices toolkit.
     * [https://github.com/goadesign/goa]Goa - Design-based HTTP
       microservices in Go.
     * [https://github.com/gocraft/web]Gocraft - A toolkit for building
       web apps. Includes routing, middleware stacks, logging and
       monitoring.
     * [https://goji.io/]Goji - Minimalistic and flexible request
       multiplexer for Go.
     * [https://github.com/go-kit/kit]Go kit - Distributed programming
       toolkit for microservices in the modern enterprise.
     * [https://github.com/micro/go-micro]Go-micro - A pluggable RPC
       microservice framework.
     * [https://github.com/bndr/gopencils]Gopencils - Easily consume REST
       APIs with Go.
     * [http://www.gorillatoolkit.org/]Gorilla - Web toolkit for the Go
       programming language.
     * [https://github.com/kataras/iris]Iris - Fast, simple and efficient
       micro web framework for Go.
     * [https://github.com/koding/kite]Kite - Microservices framework in
       Go.
     * [https://github.com/docker/libchan]Libchan - Ultra-lightweight
       networking library which lets network services communicate in the
       same way that goroutines communicate using channels.
     * [https://github.com/micro/micro]Micro - A microservices toolchain
       in Go.
     * [https://github.com/pasztorpisti/nano]Nano - A minimalistic,
       transport-agnostic and testing-friendly microservice framework.
     * [https://github.com/codegangsta/negroni]Negroni - Idiomatic HTTP
       middleware for Golang.
     * [https://github.com/neutrinoapp/neutrino]Neutrino - Realtime/REST
       backend service.
     * [https://github.com/smallnest/rpcx]RPCX - A distributed RPC service
       framework based on NET/RPC like Alibaba Dubbo and Weibo Motan.
     * [https://github.com/dougblack/sleepy]Sleepy - REST for go.
     * [https://github.com/magneticio/vamp-router]Vamp-router - Service
       routing, load balancing and filtering application.
     * [https://github.com/cosiner/zerver]Zerver - RESTful API framework.

Haskell

     * [https://github.com/scotty-web/scotty]Scotty - Micro web framework
       inspired by Ruby's Sinatra, using WAI and Warp.
     * [https://github.com/haskell-servant/servant]Servant - Type-level
       web DSL.
     * [https://github.com/yesodweb/yesod]Yesod - The Haskell RESTful web
       framework.

Java VM

Clojure

     * [https://github.com/weavejester/compojure]Compojure - A concise
       routing library for Ring/Clojure.
     * [https://github.com/weavejester/duct]Duct - Minimal framework for
       building web applications in Clojure, with a strong emphasis on
       simplicity.
     * [https://github.com/zalando/friboo]Friboo - Utility library for
       writing microservices in Clojure, with support for Swagger and
       OAuth.
     * [http://clojure-liberator.github.io/liberator/]Liberator - Library
       that helps you expose your data as resources while automatically
       complying with all the relevant requirements of the HTTP
       specification.
     * [https://modularity.org/]Modularity - JUXT's Clojure-based modular
       system.
     * [https://github.com/danielsz/system]System - Built on top of Stuart
       Sierra's component library, offers a set of readymade components.
     * [https://github.com/otto-de/tesla-microservice]Tesla - Common basis
       for some of Otto.de's Clojure microservices.

Java

     * [https://github.com/airlift/airlift]Airlift - Framework for
       building REST services in Java.
     * [https://github.com/LMAX-Exchange/disruptor]Disruptor -
       High-performance inter-thread messaging library.
     * [https://dropwizard.github.io/]Dropwizard - Java framework for
       developing ops-friendly, high-performance, RESTful web services.
     * [https://github.com/palantir/http-remoting]HTTP Remoting -
       Libraries for defining and creating RESTish/RPC servers and clients
       based on Feign or Retrofit as a client and Dropwizard/Jersey with
       JAX-RS service definitions as a server.
     * [https://github.com/Sixt/ja-micro]Ja-micro - Lightweight Java
       framework for building microservices (compatible with go-micro).
     * [https://jersey.github.io/]Jersey - RESTful services in Java.
       JAX-RS reference implementation.
     * [https://github.com/wso2/msf4j]MSF4J - High throughput & low memory
       footprint Java microservices framework.
     * [https://github.com/advantageous/qbit]QBit - Reactive programming
       library for building microservices.
     * [https://ratpack.io/]Ratpack - Set of Java libraries that
       facilitate fast, efficient, evolvable and well tested HTTP
       applications. specific support for the Groovy language is provided.
     * [http://restlet.com/]Restlet - Helps Java developers build web APIs
       that follow the REST architecture style.
     * [http://sparkjava.com/]Spark - A micro-framework for creating web
       applications in Java 8 with minimal effort.
     * [http://projects.spring.io/spring-boot/]Spring Boot - Makes it easy
       to create stand-alone, production-grade Spring based applications.

Scala

     * [http://doc.akka.io/docs/akka-http/current/scala.html]Akka HTTP -
       Open source toolkit for building REST/HTTP-based integration layers
       on top of Scala and Akka.
     * [https://github.com/tumblr/colossus]Colossus - I/O and microservice
       library for Scala.
     * [http://twitter.github.io/finatra/]Finatra - Fast, testable, Scala
       HTTP services built on Twitter-Server and Finagle.
     * [http://http4s.org/]Http4s - A minimal, idiomatic Scala interface
       for HTTP
     * [https://www.playframework.com/]Play - The high velocity web
       framework for Java and Scala.
     * [http://www.scalatra.org/]Scalatra - Simple, accessible and free
       web micro-framework.
     * [https://github.com/skinny-framework/skinny-micro]Skinny Micro -
       Micro-web framework to build servlet applications in Scala.
     * [http://paypal.github.io/squbs/]Squbs - A suite of components
       enabling standardization and operationalization of Akka and Akka
       HTTP applications/services in a large scale, managed, cloud
       environment.

Node.js

     * [http://www.actionherojs.com/]Actionhero - Multi-transport Node.js
       API server with integrated cluster capabilities and delayed tasks.
     * [https://github.com/wprl/baucis]Baucis - To build and maintain
       scalable HATEOAS/Level 3 REST APIs.
     * [https://github.com/dashersw/cote]Cote - A Node.js library for
       building zero-configuration microservices.
     * [http://expressjs.com/]Express - Fast, unopinionated, minimalist
       web framework for Node.js
     * [http://feathersjs.com/]FeathersJS - An open source REST and
       realtime API layer for modern applications.
     * [https://github.com/GraftJS/graft]Graft - Full-stack javascript
       through microservices.
     * [http://hapijs.com/]Hapi - A rich framework for building
       applications and services.
     * [https://github.com/hudson-taylor/hudson-taylor]Hudson Taylor - Set
       of libraries for building automatically documented, well validated
       services.
     * [http://koajs.com/]Koa - Next generation web framework for Node.js
     * [http://loopback.io/]Loopback - Node.js framework for creating APIs
       and easily connecting to backend data sources.
     * [http://github.com/zeithq/micro]Micro - Asynchronous HTTP
       microservices.
     * [https://github.com/zhaoyao91/micro-panda]Micro Panda - Node.js
       toolkit to help build microservices.
     * [https://github.com/czerwonkabartosz/Micro-Whalla]Micro-Whalla - A
       simple, fast framework for writing microservices in Node.js
       communicate using RPC / IPC.
     * [http://moleculer.services/]Moleculer - Fast & powerful
       microservices framework for NodeJS.
     * [http://restify.com/]Restify - Node.js module built specifically to
       enable you to build correct REST web services.
     * [http://senecajs.org/]Seneca - A microservices toolkit for Node.js
     * [https://github.com/serverless/serverless]Serverless - Build and
       maintain web, mobile and IoT applications running on AWS Lambda and
       API Gateway (formerly known as JAWS).
     * [https://github.com/99xt/steroidslibrary]Steriods Framework -
       Steroids framework simplifies the development of microservices with
       [https://github.com/serverless/serverless]Serverless using
       TypeScript by enabling the developer to emphasize more on
       business/domain logic rather than focusing too much on technical
       details.
     * [https://stdlib.com/]StdLib - Standard library for microservices.

Perl

     * [http://cro.services/]Cro - Libraries for creating reactive
       distributed systems using Perl 6.
     * [http://mojolicio.us/]Mojolicious - Next generation web framework
       for Perl.

PHP

     * [https://api-platform.com/]API Platform - API-first web framework
       on top of Symfony with JSON-LD, Schema.org and Hydra support.
     * [https://fatfreeframework.com/]Fat-Free - A powerful yet
       easy-to-use PHP micro-framework.
     * [https://github.com/mikecao/flight]Flight - An extensible
       micro-framework.
     * [http://kraken-php.com/]Kraken - Asynchronous and fault-tolerant
       PHP framework for distributed applications.
     * [https://lumen.laravel.com/]Lumen - Stunningly fast
       micro-framework.
     * [https://phalconphp.com/]Phalcon - Full-stack PHP framework
       delivered as a C-extension.
     * [http://silex.sensiolabs.org/]Silex - Micro-framework based on the
       Symfony components.
     * [http://www.slimframework.com/]Slim - Micro-framework that helps
       you quickly write simple yet powerful web applications and APIs.
     * [https://github.com/Zizaco/upswarm]Upswarm - Multi-processed,
       async, fault-tolerant micro-framework for writing service-oriented
       applications.

Python

     * [http://aiohttp.readthedocs.io/en/stable/]Aiohttp - HTTP
       client/server for asyncio.
     * [https://github.com/tomchristie/apistar]API Star - A fast and
       expressive API framework, designed for Python 3.
     * [http://flask.pocoo.org/]Flask - Python framework for microservices
       based on Werkzeug and Jinja 2.
     * [https://github.com/onefinestay/nameko]Nameko - Python framework
       for building microservices.
     * [https://github.com/channelcat/sanic]Sanic - Sanic is a Flask-like
       Python 3.5+ web server that's written to go fast.
     * [http://www.tornadoweb.org/]Tornado - Web framework and
       asynchronous networking library.
     * [https://twistedmatrix.com/trac/]Twisted - Event-driven network
       programming engine.
     * [https://github.com/webpy/webpy/]Web.py - Minimalist web framework
       for Python.
     * [https://github.com/Miserlou/Zappa]Zappa - Framework for building
       and deploying server-less Python event-driven and web applications.

Ruby

     * [https://github.com/hanami]Hanami - A modern web framework for
       Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/rightscale/praxis]Praxis - Framework for both
       designing and implementing APIs.
     * [http://edgeguides.rubyonrails.org/api_app.html]Rails API - Rails
       as an API only.
     * [https://github.com/wardrop/Scorched]Scorched - Light-weight web
       framework for Ruby.
     * [http://www.sinatrarb.com/]Sinatra - Sinatra is a DSL for quickly
       creating web applications in Ruby with minimal effort.

Capabilities

API Gateways / Edge Services

     * [https://github.com/amalgam8]Amalgam8 - Content-based routing
       fabric for polyglot microservices.
     * [https://github.com/nebo15/annon.api]Annon - Open source API
       gateway with built-in API management, authentication and status
       pages written in Elixir.
     * [https://caddyserver.com/]Caddy - Extensible HTTP/2 web server with
       automatic HTTPS.
     * [http://camel.apache.org/]Camel - Empowers you to define routing
       and mediation rules in a variety of domain-specific languages,
       including a Java-based fluent API, Spring or Blueprint XML
       configuration files, and a Scala DSL.
     * [https://github.com/lyft/envoy]Envoy - Open source edge and service
       proxy, from the developers at Lyft.
     * [https://github.com/eBay/fabio]Fabio - A fast, modern, zero-conf
       load balancing HTTP/S router for deploying microservices managed by
       Consul.
     * [http://www.haproxy.org/]HAProxy - Reliable, high Performance
       TCP/HTTP load balancer.
     * [https://istio.io/]Istio - An open platform to connect, manage, and
       secure microservices.
     * [https://github.com/hellofresh/janus]Janus - An API Gateway written
       in Go.
     * [http://www.keepalived.org/]Keepalived - Simple and robust
       facilities for loadbalancing and high-availability to Linux system
       and Linux based infrastructures.
     * [https://getkong.org/]Kong - Open source management layer for APIs.
     * [https://linkerd.io/]Linkerd - Resilient service mesh for cloud
       native apps.
     * [https://github.com/eBay/Neutrino]Neutrino - Extensible software
       load balancer.
     * [http://openresty.org/]OpenResty - Fast web application server
       built on top of Nginx.
     * [https://github.com/zalando/skipper]Skipper - HTTP router useful
       for decoupling routing from service logic.
     * [https://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-gateway/]Spring Cloud Gateway
       - API Gateway on top of Spring MVC. Aims to provide a simple, yet
       effective way to route to APIs.
     * [http://tengine.taobao.org/]Tengine - A distribution of Nginx with
       some advanced features.
     * [http://traefik.io/]TræfIk - A modern HTTP reverse proxy and load
       balancer made to deploy microservices with ease.
     * [https://github.com/apache/trafficserver]Traffic Server -
       High-performance building block for cloud services.
     * [https://tyk.io/]Tyk - Open source, fast and scalable API gateway,
       portal and API management platform.
     * [https://github.com/vulcand/vulcand]Vulcand - Programmatic load
       balancer backed by Etcd.
     * [https://github.com/Netflix/zuul]Zuul - An edge service that
       provides dynamic routing, monitoring, resiliency, security, and
       more.

Configuration and Discovery

     * [https://www.consul.io/]Consul - Service discovery and
       configuration made easy. Distributed, highly available, and
       datacenter-aware.
     * [https://github.com/joyent/containerpilot]ContainerPilot - Service
       for autodiscovery and configuration of applications running in
       containers.
     * [https://github.com/Netflix/denominator]Denominator - Portably
       control DNS clouds using java or bash.
     * [https://github.com/ha/doozerd]Doozer - Highly-available,
       completely consistent store for small amounts of data. When the
       data changes, it can notify connected clients immediately.
     * [https://github.com/coreos/etcd]Etcd - Highly-available key-value
       store for shared configuration and service discovery.
     * [https://github.com/Netflix/eureka/wiki/Eureka-at-a-glance]Eureka -
       REST based service that is primarily used in the AWS cloud for
       locating services for the purpose of load balancing and failover of
       middle-tier servers.
     * [https://github.com/rogeralsing/Microphone]Microphone - Lightweight
       .NET framework to run self hosting REST services using Web Api or
       NancyFx on top of a Consul or Etcd cluster.
     * [https://github.com/gliderlabs/registrator]Registrator - Service
       registry bridge for Docker. Supports pluggable service registries,
       which currently includes Consul, Etcd and SkyDNS 2.
     * [https://github.com/nanopack/shaman]Shaman - Small, lightweight,
       api-driven DNS server.
     * [https://github.com/skynetservices/skydns]SkyDNS - Distributed
       service for announcement and discovery of services built on top of
       etcd. It utilizes DNS queries to discover available services.
     * [https://github.com/airbnb/smartstack-cookbook]SmartStack -
       Airbnb's automated service discovery and registration framework.
     * [http://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-config/]Spring Cloud Config -
       Provides server and client-side support for externalized
       configuration in a distributed system.
     * [https://zookeeper.apache.org/]ZooKeeper - Open source server which
       enables highly reliable distributed coordination.

Coordination and Governance

     * [https://aws.amazon.com/step-functions/]AWS Step Functions c -
       Coordinate the components of distributed applications and
       microservices using visual workflows.
     * [https://azuqua.com/]Azuqua c - Orchestration and governance
       platform for distributed applications.
     * [https://github.com/Netflix/conductor]Conductor - A microservices
       orchestration engine.
     * [https://github.com/fission/fission-workflows]Fission Workflows -
       Workflow-based, reliable function composition for serverless
       functions.

Elasticity

     * [http://www.paralleluniverse.co/galaxy/]Galaxy - Open source
       high-performance in-memory data-grid.
     * [http://reverbrain.com/grape/]Grape - Realtime processing pipeline.
     * [http://hazelcast.org/]Hazelcast - Open source in-memory data-grid.
       Allows you to distribute data and computation across servers,
       clusters and geographies, and to manage very large data sets or
       high data ingest rates. Mature technology.
     * [http://helix.apache.org/]Helix - Generic cluster management
       framework used for the automatic management of partitioned,
       replicated and distributed resources hosted on a cluster of nodes.
     * [http://ignite.apache.org/]Ignite - High-performance, integrated
       and distributed in-memory platform for computing and transacting on
       large-scale data sets in real-time, orders of magnitude faster than
       possible with traditional disk-based or flash technologies.
     * [https://mesosphere.github.io/marathon/]Marathon - Deploy and
       manage containers (including Docker) on top of Apache Mesos at
       scale.
     * [https://mesos.apache.org/]Mesos - Abstracts CPU, memory, storage,
       and other compute resources away from machines (physical or
       virtual), enabling fault-tolerant and elastic distributed systems
       to easily be built and run effectively.
     * [https://www.nomadproject.io/]Nomad - Distributed, highly
       available, datacenter-aware scheduler.
     * [https://github.com/onyx-platform/onyx]Onyx - Distributed,
       masterless, high performance, fault tolerant data processing for
       Clojure.
     * [https://github.com/boundary/ordasity]Ordasity - Designed to spread
       persistent or long-lived workloads across several machines.
     * [https://github.com/mrniko/redisson]Redisson - Distributed and
       scalable Java data structures on top of Redis server.
     * [https://www.serfdom.io/]Serf - Decentralized solution for cluster
       membership, failure detection and orchestration.

Job Schedulers / Workload Automation

     * [http://www.celeryproject.org/]Celery - Asynchronous task queue/job
       queue based on distributed message passing. Focused on real-time
       operation and supports scheduling.
     * [https://github.com/mesos/chronos]Chronos - Fault tolerant job
       scheduler for Mesos which handles dependencies and ISO8601 based
       schedules.
     * [https://github.com/Netflix/Fenzo]Fenzo - Extensible scheduler for
       Mesos frameworks.
     * [http://www.sos-berlin.com/jobscheduler]JobScheduler - Open Source
       solution for enterprise-level workload automation. It is used to
       launch executable files and shell scripts and to run database
       procedures automatically.
     * [http://rundeck.org/]Rundeck - Job scheduler and runbook
       automation. Enable self-service access to existing scripts and
       tools.
     * [http://www.schedulix.org/en]Schedulix - Open source enterprise job
       scheduling system lays down ground-breaking standards for the
       professional automation of IT processes in advanced system
       environments.

Logging

     * [https://github.com/trentm/node-bunyan]Bunyan - Simple and fast
       JSON logging library for Node.js services.
     * [http://www.fluentd.org/]Fluentd - Open source data collector for
       unified logging layer.
     * [https://www.graylog.org/]Graylog - Fully integrated open source
       log management platform.
     * [https://www.elastic.co/products/kibana]Kibana - Flexible analytics
       and visualization platform.
     * [https://www.elastic.co/products/logstash]Logstash - Tool for
       managing events and logs.
     * [https://github.com/Netflix/suro/wiki]Suro - Distributed data
       pipeline which enables services for moving, aggregating, routing,
       storing data.

Messaging

     * [http://zeromq.org/]ØMQ - Brokerless intelligent transport layer.
     * [http://activemq.apache.org/]ActiveMQ - Powerful open source
       messaging and integration patterns server.
     * [https://github.com/real-logic/Aeron]Aeron - Efficient reliable UDP
       unicast, UDP multicast, and IPC message transport.
     * [http://activemq.apache.org/apollo/]Apollo - Faster, more reliable,
       easier to maintain messaging broker built from the foundations of
       the original ActiveMQ.
     * [https://github.com/mcollina/ascoltatori]Ascoltatori - Pub/sub
       library for Node.
     * [http://kr.github.io/beanstalkd/]Beanstalk - Simple, fast work
       queue.
     * [https://github.com/antirez/disque]Disque - Distributed message
       broker.
     * [http://kafka.apache.org/]Kafka - Publish-subscribe messaging
       rethought as a distributed commit log.
     * [https://github.com/zeromq/malamute]Malamute - ZeroMQ enterprise
       messaging broker.
     * [https://github.com/nanopack/mist]Mist - A distributed, tag-based
       pub/sub service.
     * [http://www.mosca.io/]Mosca - MQTT broker as a module.
     * [http://mosquitto.org/]Mosquitto - Open source message broker that
       implements the MQTT protocol.
     * [http://nanomsg.org/]Nanomsg - Socket library that provides several
       common communication patterns for building distributed systems.
     * [https://nats.io/]NATS - Open source, high-performance, lightweight
       cloud messaging system.
     * [http://nsq.io/]NSQ - A realtime distributed messaging platform.
     * [https://qpid.apache.org/]Qpid - Cross-platform messaging
       components built on AMQP.
     * [https://www.rabbitmq.com/]RabbitMQ - Open source Erlang-based
       message broker that just works.
     * [https://github.com/apache/incubator-rocketmq]RocketMQ - A low
       latency, reliable, scalable, easy to use message oriented
       middleware born from alibaba massive messaging business.
     * [https://verne.mq/]VerneMQ - Open source, scalable, Erlang-based
       MQTT broker.

Monitoring and Debugging

     * [https://www.elastic.co/products/beats]Beats - Lightweight shippers
       for Elasticsearch & Logstash.
     * [https://collectd.org/]Collectd - The system statistics collection
       daemon.
     * [https://github.com/yelp/elastalert]Elastalert - Easy & flexible
       alerting for Elasticsearch.
     * [http://ganglia.info/]Ganglia - A scalable distributed monitoring
       system for high-performance computing systems such as clusters and
       grids.
     * [http://grafana.org/]Grafana - An open source, feature rich metrics
       dashboard and graph editor for Graphite, InfluxDB & OpenTSDB.
     * [http://graphite.wikidot.com/]Graphite - Scalable realtime
       graphing.
     * [https://www.iopipe.com/]IOpipe c - Application performance
       monitoring for Amazon Lambda.
     * [https://github.com/eBay/parallec]Parallec - Fast parallel
       asynchronous HTTP/SSH/TCP/Ping client Java library.
     * [http://prometheus.io/]Prometheus - An open source service
       monitoring system and time series database.
     * [https://github.com/eBay/restcommander]REST Commander - Fast
       parallel asynchronous HTTP client as a service to monitor and
       manage HTTP endpoints.
     * [http://riemann.io/]Riemann - Monitors distributed systems.
     * [https://github.com/sensu]Sensu - Monitoring for today's
       infrastructure.
     * [https://github.com/RisingStack/trace-nodejs]Trace - A visualised
       stack trace platform designed for microservices.
     * [https://www.elastic.co/products/watcher]Watcher - Alerting for
       Elasticsearch.
     * [http://www.zabbix.com/]Zabbix - Open source enterprise-class
       monitoring solution.
     * [http://zipkin.io/]Zipkin - Distributed tracing system.

Reactivity

     * [http://projectreactor.io/]Reactor.io - A second-generation
       Reactive library for building non-blocking applications on the JVM
       based on the Reactive Streams Specification.
     * [https://github.com/softwaremill/reactive-kafka]Reactive Kafka -
       Reactive Streams API for Apache Kafka.
     * [http://reactivex.io/]ReactiveX - API for asynchronous programming
       with observable streams. Available for idiomatic Java, Scala, C#,
       C++, Clojure, JavaScript, Python, Groovy, JRuby, and others.
     * [https://github.com/aol/simple-react]Simple React - Powerful future
       streams & asynchronous data structures for Java 8.

Resilience

     * [https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix]Hystrix - Latency and fault
       tolerance library designed to isolate points of access to remote
       systems, services and 3rd party libraries, stop cascading failure
       and enable resilience in complex distributed systems where failure
       is inevitable.
     * [http://pathod.net/]Pathod - Crafted malice for tormenting HTTP
       clients and servers.
     * [http://raftconsensus.github.io/]Raft Consensus - Consensus
       algorithm that is designed to be easy to understand. It's
       equivalent to Paxos in fault-tolerance and performance.
     * [http://resilient-http.github.io/]Resilient HTTP - A smart HTTP
       client with super powers like fault tolerance, dynamic server
       discovery, auto balancing and reactive recovery, designed for
       distributed systems.
     * [https://github.com/tomakehurst/saboteur]Saboteur - Causing
       deliberate network mayhem for better resilience.
     * [https://github.com/Shopify/semian]Semian - Resiliency toolkit for
       Ruby for failing fast.
     * [https://github.com/Netflix/SimianArmy]Simian Army - Suite of tools
       for keeping your cloud operating in top form. Chaos Monkey, the
       first member, is a resiliency tool that helps ensure that your
       applications can tolerate random instance failures.
     * [https://github.com/shopify/toxiproxy]Toxiproxy - TCP proxy to
       simulate network and system conditions for chaos and resiliency
       testing.

Security

     * [https://github.com/spotify/crtauth]Crtauth - A public key backed
       client/server authentication system.
     * [https://github.com/coreos/dex]Dex - Opinionated auth/directory
       service with pluggable connectors. OpenID Connect provider and
       third-party OAuth 2.0 delegation.
     * [http://jwt.io/]JWT - JSON Web Tokens are an open, industry
       standard RFC 7519 method for representing claims securely between
       two parties.
     * [https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak]Keycloak - Full-featured and
       extensible auth service. OpenID Connect provider and third-party
       OAuth 2.0 delegation.
     * [https://github.com/networknt/light-oauth2]Light OAuth2 - A fast,
       lightweight and cloud native OAuth 2.0 authorization microservices
       based on light-java.
     * [https://github.com/lipp/login-with]Login With - Stateless
       login-with microservice for Google, FB, Github, and more.
     * [http://oauth.net/2/]OAuth - Provides specific authorization flows
       for web applications, desktop applications, mobile phones, and
       living room devices. Many implementations.
     * [http://openid.net/developers/libraries/]OpenID Connect -
       Libraries, products, and tools implementing current OpenID
       specifications and related specs.
     * [https://github.com/osiam/osiam]OSIAM - Open source identity and
       access management implementing OAuth 2.0 and SCIMv2.
     * [http://www.simplecloud.info/]SCIM - System for Cross-domain
       Identity Management.
     * [https://www.vaultproject.io/]Vault - Secures, stores, and tightly
       controls access to tokens, passwords, certificates, API keys, and
       other secrets in modern computing.

Serialization

     * [https://avro.apache.org/]Avro - Apache data serialization system
       providing rich data structures in a compact, fast, binary data
       format.
     * [https://github.com/ochrons/boopickle]BooPickle - Binary
       serialization library for efficient network communication. For
       Scala and Scala.js
     * [https://capnproto.org/]Cap'n Proto - Insanely fast data
       interchange format and capability-based RPC system.
     * [http://cbor.io/]CBOR - Implementations of the CBOR standard (RFC
       7049) in many languages.
     * [http://uscilab.github.io/cereal/]Cereal - C++11 library for
       serialization.
     * [https://github.com/dakrone/cheshire]Cheshire - Clojure JSON and
       JSON SMILE encoding/decoding.
     * [http://etch.apache.org/]Etch - Cross-platform, language and
       transport-independent framework for building and consuming network
       services.
     * [https://github.com/alibaba/fastjson]Fastjson - Fast JSON
       Processor.
     * [https://github.com/pquerna/ffjson]Ffjson - Faster JSON
       serialization for Go.
     * [https://github.com/RuedigerMoeller/fast-serialization]FST - Fast
       java serialization drop in-replacemen.
     * [https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson]Jackson - A multi-purpose
       Java library for processing JSON data format.
     * [https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-module-afterburner]Jackson
       Afterburner - Jackson module that uses bytecode generation to
       further speed up data binding (+30-40% throughput for
       serialization, deserialization).
     * [https://github.com/EsotericSoftware/kryo]Kryo - Java serialization
       and cloning: fast, efficient, automatic.
     * [http://msgpack.org/]MessagePack - Efficient binary serialization
       format.
     * [https://github.com/protostuff/protostuff]Protostuff - A
       serialization library with built-in support for forward-backward
       compatibility (schema evolution) and validation.
     * [https://github.com/harrah/sbinary]SBinary - Library for describing
       binary formats for Scala types.
     * [http://thrift.apache.org/]Thrift - The Apache Thrift software
       framework, for scalable cross-language services development.

Storage

     * [https://hive.apache.org/]Apache Hive - Data warehouse
       infrastructure built on top of Hadoop.
     * [http://cassandra.apache.org/]Apache Cassandra - Column-oriented
       and providing high availability with no single point of failure.
     * [http://hbase.apache.org/]Apache HBase - Hadoop database for big
       data.
     * [http://www.aerospike.com/]Aerospike c - High performance NoSQL
       database delivering speed at scale.
     * [https://www.arangodb.com/]ArangoDB - A distributed free and open
       source database with a flexible data model for documents, graphs,
       and key-values.
     * [https://github.com/palantir/atlasdb]AtlasDB - Transactional layer
       on top of a key value store.
     * [https://clickhouse.yandex/]ClickHouse - Column-oriented database
       management system that allows generating analytical data reports in
       real time.
     * [https://www.cockroachlabs.com/product/cockroachdb-core/]CockroachD
       B c - A cloud-native SQL database modelled after Google Spanner.
     * [http://www.couchbase.com/]Couchbase - A distributed database
       engineered for performance, scalability, and simplified
       administration.
     * [https://crate.io/]Crate c - Scalable SQL database with the NoSQL
       goodies.
     * [http://www.datomic.com/]Datomic - Fully transactional,
       cloud-ready, distributed database.
     * [http://druid.io/]Druid - Fast column-oriented distributed data
       store.
     * [https://www.elastic.co/products/elasticsearch]Elasticsearch - Open
       source distributed, scalable, and highly available search server.
     * [http://reverbrain.com/elliptics/]Elliptics - Fault tolerant
       distributed key/value storage.
     * [http://geode.incubator.apache.org/]Geode - Open source,
       distributed, in-memory database for scale-out applications.
     * [http://infinispan.org/]Infinispan - Highly concurrent key/value
       datastore used for caching.
     * [https://github.com/influxdata/influxdb]InfluxDB - Scalable
       datastore for metrics, events, and real-time analytics.
     * [https://www.joyent.com/manta]Manta - Highly scalable, distributed
       object storage service with integrated compute.
     * [http://www.memsql.com/]MemSQL c - High-performance, in-memory
       database that combines the horizontal scalability of distributed
       systems with the familiarity of SQL.
     * [http://opentsdb.net/]OpenTSDB - Scalable and distributed time
       series database written on top of Apache HBase.
     * [https://parquet.apache.org/]Parquet - Columnar storage format
       available to any project in the Hadoop ecosystem, regardless of the
       choice of data processing framework, data model or programming
       language.
     * [https://github.com/reborndb/reborn]Reborn - Distributed database
       fully compatible with redis protocol.
     * [http://rethinkdb.com/]RethinkDB - Open source, scalable database
       that makes building realtime apps easier.
     * [https://github.com/ssbc/docs]Secure Scuttlebutt - P2P database of
       message-feeds.
     * [http://tachyon-project.org/]Tachyon - Memory-centric distributed
       storage system, enabling reliable data sharing at memory-speed
       across cluster frameworks.
     * [https://github.com/voldemort/voldemort]Voldemort - Open source
       clone of Amazon DynamoDB
     * [https://www.voltdb.com/]VoltDB c - In-Memory ACID compliant
       distributed database.

Testing

     * [https://github.com/buger/goreplay]Goreplay - A tool for capturing
       and replaying live HTTP traffic into a test environment.
     * [https://mitmproxy.org/]Mitmproxy - An interactive console program
       that allows traffic flows to be intercepted, inspected, modified
       and replayed.
     * [http://www.mbtest.org/]Mountebank - Cross-platform, multi-protocol
       test doubles over the wire.
     * [https://cloud.spring.io/spring-cloud-contract/]Spring Cloud
       Contract - TDD to the level of software architecture.
     * [https://github.com/vcr/vcr]VCR - Record your test suite's HTTP
       interactions and replay them during future test runs for fast,
       deterministic, accurate tests. See the list of ports for
       implementations in other languages.
     * [https://github.com/epam/Wilma]Wilma - Combined HTTP/HTTPS service
       stub and transparent proxy solution.
     * [http://wiremock.org/]WireMock - Flexible library for stubbing and
       mocking web services. Unlike general purpose mocking tools it works
       by creating an actual HTTP server that your code under test can
       connect to as it would a real web service.

