Documentation & Modeling

REST APIs

     * [https://github.com/danielgtaylor/aglio]Aglio - API Blueprint
       renderer with theme support that outputs static HTML.
     * [https://apiblueprint.org/]API Blueprint - Tools for your whole API
       lifecycle. Use it to discuss your API with others. Generate
       documentation automatically. Or a test suite. Or even some code.
     * [https://github.com/mbryzek/apidoc]Apidoc - Beautiful documentation
       for REST services.
     * [http://raml.org/]RAML - RESTful API Modeling Language, a simple
       and succinct way of describing practically-RESTful APIs.
     * [https://github.com/tripit/slate]Slate - Beautiful static
       documentation for your API.
     * [http://projects.spring.io/spring-restdocs/]Spring REST Docs -
       Document RESTful services by combining hand-written documentation
       with auto-generated snippets produced with Spring MVC Test.
     * [http://swagger.io/]Swagger - A simple yet powerful representation
       of your RESTful API.

Standards / Recommendations

World Wide Web

     * [http://www.w3.org/TR/webarch/]W3C.REC-Webarch - Architecture of
       the World Wide Web, Volume One.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986]RFC3986 - Uniform Resource
       Identifier (URI): Generic Syntax.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6570]RFC6570 - URI Template.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7320]RFC7320 - URI Design and
       Ownership.

HTTP/1.1

     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7230]RFC7230 - Message Syntax and
       Routing.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231]RFC7231 - Semantics and
       Content.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7232]RFC7232 - Conditional
       Requests.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7233]RFC7233 - Range Requests.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7234]RFC7234 - Caching.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7235]RFC7235 - Authentication.

HTTP/2

     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7540]RFC7540 - Hypertext Transfer
       Protocol Version 2.

CoAP

     * [http://coap.technology/spec.html]RFC7252 - The Constrained
       Application Protocol (CoAP) is a specialized web transfer protocol
       for use with constrained nodes and constrained networks in the
       Internet of Things.

RPC

     * [http://bert-rpc.org/]BERT-RPC 1.0 - An attempt to specify a
       flexible binary serialization and RPC protocol that are compatible
       with the philosophies of dynamic languages.
     * [http://www.jsonrpc.org/specification]JSON-RPC 2.0 - A stateless,
       light-weight remote procedure call (RPC) protocol.

Messaging

     * [http://www.amqp.org/]AMQP - Advanced Message Queuing Protocol.
     * [http://mqtt.org/]MQTT - MQ Telemetry Transport.
     * [https://stomp.github.io/]STOMP - Simple Text Oriented Messaging
       Protocol.

Security

     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5246]RFC5246 - The Transport Layer
       Security (TLS) Protocol Version 1.2.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6066]RFC6066 - TLS Extensions.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6347]RFC6347 - Datagram Transport
       Layer Security Version 1.2.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749]RFC6749 - The OAuth 2.0
       authorization framework.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7515]RFC7515 - JSON Web Signature
       (JWS) represents content secured with digital signatures or Message
       Authentication Codes (MACs) using JSON-based data structures.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519]RFC7519 - JSON Web Token (JWT)
       is a compact, URL-safe means of representing claims to be
       transferred between two parties.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7642]RFC7642 - SCIM: Definitions,
       overview, concepts, and requirements.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7643]RFC7643 - SCIM: Core Schema,
       provides a platform-neutral schema and extension model for
       representing users and groups.
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7644]RFC7644 - SCIM: Protocol, an
       application-level, REST protocol for provisioning and managing
       identity data on the web.
     * [http://openid.net/connect/]OIDCONN - OpenID Connect 1.0 is a
       simple identity layer on top of the OAuth 2.0 protocol. It allows
       clients to verify the identity of the end-user based on the
       authentication performed by an Authorization Server, as well as to
       obtain basic profile information about the end-user in an
       interoperable and REST-like manner.

Service Discovery

     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-kelly-json-hal-07]HAL - The JSON
       Hypertext Application Language (HAL) is a standard which
       establishes conventions for expressing hypermedia controls, such as
       links, with JSON. ^DRAFT
     * [http://www.hydra-cg.com/]Hydra - Specifications for interoperable,
       hypermedia-driven Web APIs.
     * [http://graphql.org/]GraphQL - Query language designed to build
       client applications by providing an intuitive and flexible syntax
       and system for describing their data requirements and interactions.
       ^DRAFT
     * [http://www.w3.org/Submission/wadl/]WADL - The Web Application
       Description Language specification.
     * [http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl20/]WSDL - The Web Services Description
       Language Version 2.0 spec.

Data Formats

     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc4627]RFC4627 - JavaScript Object
       Notation (JSON).
     * [http://tools.ietf.org/search/rfc7049]RFC7049 - Concise Binary
       Object Representation (CBOR).
     * [http://bsonspec.org/]BSON - Binary JSON (BSON).
     * [http://json-ld.org/]JSON-LD - JSON for Linking Data.
     * [https://github.com/FIXTradingCommunity/fix-simple-binary-encoding]
       SBE - Simple Binary Encoding (SBE).
     * [https://github.com/msgpack/msgpack/blob/master/spec.md]MSGPACK -
       MessagePack Specification.
     * [http://ubjson.org/]UBJSON - Universal Binary JSON Specification.

Vocabularies

     * [http://json-schema.org/]JSON Schema - Vocabulary that allows you
       to annotate and validate JSON documents.
     * [http://lov.okfn.org/]LOV - Linked open vocabularies.
     * [http://schema.org/]Schema.org - Collaborative, community activity
       with a mission to create, maintain, and promote schemas for
       structured data on the Internet, on web pages, in email messages,
       and beyond.

Unicode

     * [http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode8.0.0/]UNIV8 - The Unicode
       Consortium. The Unicode Standard, Version 8.0.0, (Mountain View,
       CA: The Unicode Consortium, 2015. ISBN 978-1-936213-10-8).
     * [https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3629]RFC3629 - UTF-8, a
       transformation format of ISO 10646.

