Theory

Articles & Papers

     * [http://akfpartners.com/techblog/2008/05/08/splitting-applications-
       or-services-for-scale/]AKF Scale Cube - Model depicting the
       dimensions to scale a service.
     * [https://goo.gl/14ElnV]Benchmark Requirements for Microservices
       Architecture Research ¸^PDF - Set of requirements that may be
       useful in selecting a community-owned architecture benchmark to
       support repeatable microservices research.
     * [https://cloudncode.blog/2016/07/22/msa-getting-started/]Building
       Microservices? Here is What You Should Know - A practical overview,
       based on real-world experience, of what one would need to know in
       order to build Microservices.
     * [http://db.cs.berkeley.edu/papers/cidr11-bloom.pdf]CALM ¸^PDF -
       Consistency as logical monotonicity.
     * [http://martinfowler.com/bliki/CanaryRelease.html]Canary Release -
       Technique to reduce the risk of introducing a new software version
       in production by slowly rolling out the change to a small subset of
       users before rolling it out to the entire infrastructure and making
       it available to everybody.
     * [http://blog.thislongrun.com/2015/03/the-cap-theorem-series.html]CA
       P Theorem - States that it is impossible for a distributed computer
       system to simultaneously provide all three of the following
       guarantees: Consistency, Availability and Partition tolerance.
     * [https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/dn600223.aspx]Cloud
       Design Patterns - Contains twenty-four design patterns that are
       useful in cloud-hosted applications. Includes: Circuit Breaker,
       Competing Consumers, CQRS, Event Sourcing, Gatekeeper, Cache-Aside,
       etc.
     * [http://alistair.cockburn.us/Hexagonal+architecture]Hexagonal
       Architecture - Allows an application to equally be driven by users,
       programs, automated test or batch scripts, and to be developed and
       tested in isolation from its eventual run-time devices and
       databases.
     * [http://martinfowler.com/articles/microservices.html]Microservice
       Architecture - Particular way of designing software applications as
       suites of independently deployable services.
     * [http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/issue-archive/2015/15-mar/o25arc
       hitect-2458702.html]Microservices and SOA - Similarities,
       differences, and where we go from here.
     * [http://basho.com/posts/technical/microservices-please-dont/]Micros
       ervices - Please, don't - Critical advice about some problems
       regarding a microservices approach.
     * [https://dzone.com/refcardz/getting-started-with-microservices]Micr
       oservices RefCard - Getting started with microservices.
     * [http://martinfowler.com/articles/microservice-trade-offs.html]Micr
       oservices Trade-Offs - Guide to ponder costs and benefits of the
       mircoservices architectural style.
     * [http://www.reactivemanifesto.org/]Reactive Manifesto - Reactive
       systems definition.
     * [http://www.reactive-streams.org/]Reactive Streams - Initiative to
       provide a standard for asynchronous stream processing with
       non-blocking back pressure.
     * [http://resources.1060research.com/docs/2015/Resource-Oriented-Comp
       uting-Adaptive-Systems-ROCAS-1.2.pdf]ROCAS ¸^PDF - Resource
       Oriented Computing for Adaptive Systems.
     * [http://ceur-ws.org/Vol-746/IWSECO2011-6-DengYu.pdf]SECO ¸^PDF -
       Understanding software ecosystems: a strategic modeling approach.
     * [https://www.nginx.com/blog/service-discovery-in-a-microservices-ar
       chitecture/]Service Discovery in a Microservice Architecture -
       Overview of discovery and registration patterns.
     * [http://martinfowler.com/articles/microservice-testing/]Testing
       Strategies in a Microservice Architecture - Approaches for managing
       the additional testing complexity of multiple independently
       deployable components.
     * [http://monkey.org/%7Emarius/funsrv.pdf]Your Server as a Function
       ¸^PDF - Describes three abstractions which combine to present a
       powerful programming model for building safe, modular, and
       efficient server software: Composable futures, services and
       filters.

Talks

     * [http://jonasboner.com/bla-bla-microservices-bla-bla/]Bla Bla
       Microservices Bla Bla - A talk at the O'Reilly Software
       Architecture Conference, April 2016.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yPf5MfOZPY0]Challenges in
       Implementing MicroServices - A presentation at GOTO 2015 by Fred
       George.
     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wgdBVIX9ifA]Microservices - A
       presentation at GOTO Berlin 2014 by Martin Fowler.

Tutorials

     * [http://www.skybert.net/python/developing-a-restful-micro-service-i
       n-python/]Developing a RESTful Microservice in Python - A story of
       how an aging Java project was replaced with a microservice built
       with Python and Flask.
     * [http://mherman.org/blog/2017/04/18/developing-and-testing-microser
       vices-with-docker]Developing and Testing Microservices With Docker
       - An example of the processes involved in creating a simple
       Docker-packaged Node microservice.
     * [https://game-on.org/]Game On! - Microservices architecture
       explained in the context of an old-school text-based adventure
       game.
     * [https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/compute/microservices-without-the-ser
       vers/]Microservices without the Servers - Step by step demo-driven
       talk about serverless architecture.
     * Microservices in C#:
       [http://insidethecpu.com/2015/07/17/microservices-in-c-part-1-build
       ing-and-testing/]Part 1,
       [http://insidethecpu.com/2015/07/31/microservices-in-c-part-2-consi
       stent-message-delivery/]Part 2,
       [http://insidethecpu.com/2015/08/14/microservices-in-c-part-3-queue
       -pool-sizing/]Part 3,
       [http://insidethecpu.com/2015/08/28/microservices-in-c-part-4-scali
       ng-out/]Part 4,
       [http://insidethecpu.com/2015/09/11/microservices-in-c-part-5-autos
       caling/]Part 5.
     * [http://brunorocha.org/python/microservices-with-python-rabbitmq-an
       d-nameko.html]Microservices with Python, RabbitMQ and Nameko
     * [https://github.com/theiterators/reactive-microservices]Reactive
       Microservices - Project showcasing different microservice
       communication styles using Scala, Akka, Play and other tools from
       Scala ecosystem.
     * [https://blog.codeship.com/packer-ansible/]Using Packer and Ansible
       to build immutable infrastructure

Books

     * [https://www.nginx.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Building_Microser
       vices_Nginx.pdf]Building Microservices ¸^PDF - Building
       Microservices: Designing Fine-grained Systems. Sam Newman. Preview
       Edition.
     * [http://shop.oreilly.com/product/0636920050308.do]Microservice
       Architecture: Aligning Principles, Practices, and Culture -
       Practical advice for the strategy and design of Microservices.
     * [https://www.manning.com/books/microservices-in-action]Microservice
       s in Action - A practical book about building and deploying
       microservice-based applications.
     * [https://www.manning.com/books/microservice-patterns]Microservice
       Patterns - Teaches how to build applications with the microservice
       architecture and how to refactor a monolithic application to a
       microservices.
     * [http://www.redbooks.ibm.com/abstracts/sg248275.html?Open]Microserv
       ices from Theory to Practice - Microservices from Theory to
       Practice: Creating Applications in IBM Bluemix Using the
       Microservices Approach. IBM Redbooks publication.
     * [http://pivotal.io/platform/migrating-to-cloud-native-application-a
       rchitectures-ebook]Migrating to Cloud Native Application
       Architectures - This O'Reilly report defines the unique
       characteristics of cloud native application architectures such as
       microservices and twelve-factor applications.
     * [https://www.manning.com/books/testing-microservices-with-mounteban
       k]Testing Microservices with Mountebank - Provides a testing
       strategy using mountebank for service virtualization, promoting
       independent releases of Microservices
     * [http://theartofscalability.com/]The Art of Scalability - The Art
       of Scalability: Scalable Web Architecture, Processes, and
       Organizations for the Modern Enterprise. Martin L. Abbott, Michael
       T. Fisher.
     * [http://thenewstack.io/ebookseries/]The New Stack eBook Series - A
       Comprehensive Overview of the Docker and Container Ecosystem.
          + Book 1: The Docker Container Ecosystem.
          + Book 2: Applications & Microservices with Docker & Containers.
          + Book 3: Automation & Orchestration with Docker & Containers.
          + Book 4: Network, Security & Storage with Docker & Containers.
          + Book 5: Monitoring & Management with Docker & Containers.
     * [https://www.manning.com/books/the-tao-of-microservices]The Tao of
       Microservices - Teaches the path to understanding how to apply
       microservices architecture with your own real-world projects.

Sites

     * [http://martinfowler.com/microservices/]Microservices Resource
       Guide - Martin Fowler's choice of articles, videos, books, and
       podcasts that can teach you more about the microservices
       architectural style.
     * [http://microservices.io/]Microservice Patterns - Microservice
       architecture patterns and best practices.
     * [https://www.oreilly.com/ideas/microservices-antipatterns-and-pitfa
       lls]Microservice Antipatterns and Pitfalls - Microservice mostly
       known antipatterns and pitfalls.
     * [http://12factor.net/]The 12-Factors App - A methodology for
       building software-as-a-service applications.

Emerging Technologies

     * [https://www.bigchaindb.com/]BigchainDB - The scalable blockchain
       database.
     * [http://blocknet.co/]Blocknet - The Blocknet makes possible to
       deliver microservices over a blockchain-based P2P network
       architecture.
     * [https://blockstack.org/]Blockstack - A new decentralized internet
       where users control their data and apps run on their devices.
     * [http://ceptr.org/]CEPTR - A recomposable medium for distributed
       social computing, a semantic self-describing protocol stack, and a
       cretor of fractal coherence contexts for biomimetic computing.
     * [http://edgware-fabric.org/]Edgware Fabric - Lightweight, agile
       service bus for systems at the edge of the network, in the physical
       world.
     * [https://www.hyperledger.org/]Hyperledger - Open source
       collaborative effort created to advance cross-industry blockchain
       technologies. It is a global collaboration, hosted by The Linux
       Foundation, including leaders in finance, banking, IoT, supply
       chain, manufacturing and technology.
     * [http://www.luna-lang.org/]Luna - Visual and textual functional
       programming language with a focus on productivity, collaboration
       and development ergonomics.
     * [http://www.multichain.com/]MultiChain - Open platform for building
       blockchains.
     * [http://nodered.org/]Node-RED - Visual tool for wiring together
       hardware devices, APIs and online services in new and interesting
       ways.
     * [http://www.ponylang.org/]Pony - Open source, object-oriented,
       actor-model, capabilities-secure, high performance programming
       language.

